nd_maintain_a_great_company_culture_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263036 320w" width="2186" height="1565" alt="How to build, nurture and maintain a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="How to build, nurture and maintain a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-18_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4549" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-lkgTHX jrzygT pf-19_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fmBCVi iwpzju"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-20_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-21_"><p class="sc-fXeWAj hLqvjI pf-22_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-24_">In an increasingly competitive corporate world, having an edge means more than just offering a unique product or service; it involves creating and maintaining a robust company culture.<br><br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> argues that company culture is pivotal in attracting top talent, retaining employees, and fostering innovation. But how does one build such a culture? Let's dive in.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-27_">Understand what "culture" really means</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_what_culture_really_means_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263136" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_what_culture_really_means_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263136 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_what_culture_really_means_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263136 320w" width="1728" height="1152" alt="Understand what "culture" really means - Positive company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understand what "culture" really means - Positive company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-28_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-fXeWAj hLqvjI pf-29_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-31_">Before you can cultivate a great culture, it's crucial to understand what culture is. At its core, company culture is the shared values, behaviours, and practices that shape and reflect an organisation's broader ethos. It's the heartbeat of a company—the intangible energy that dictates how work gets done and how people interact. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-34_">Start with leadership </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Start_with_leadership_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263245" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Start_with_leadership_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263245 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Start_with_leadership_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263245 320w" width="2579" height="1702" alt="Start with leadership - Building a positive company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Start with leadership - Building a positive company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-35_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-fXeWAj hLqvjI pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-38_">As leadership goes, so goes the rest of the company. Leaders set the tone, and their actions, behaviours, and decisions are mirrored by those further down the hierarchy. To cultivate a positive company culture: </span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-cbTzjv cdRhtw pf-39_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-40_ pf-text-1">Lead by example. Be a living embodiment of the company’s values.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-42_ pf-text-1">Promote open communication. Foster an environment where employees feel comfortable sharing ideas without fear of retribution.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-44_ pf-text-1">Invest in leadership training. Equip your leadership team with the tools to be effective culture builders.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-46_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-48_">Prioritise hiring the right people</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Prioritise_hiring_the_right_people_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263343" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Prioritise_hiring_the_right_people_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263343 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Prioritise_hiring_the_right_people_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263343 320w" width="1646" height="1097" alt="Prioritise hiring the right people - How to hire the correct people - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Prioritise hiring the right people - How to hire the correct people - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-49_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-fXeWAj hLqvjI pf-50_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-52_">The importance of hiring the right people cannot be overstated. Hiring should be a reflection of the culture you wish to cultivate:</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-cbTzjv cdRhtw pf-53_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-54_ pf-text-1">Look beyond the CV. While skills are essential, attitude and alignment with company values matter more.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-56_ pf-text-1">Onboarding matters. The initial days of an employee in the company are crucial. Use this period to introduce them to the company culture, making them feel welcome and valued.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-58_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-60_">Open channels of communication</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Open_channels_of_communication_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263448" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Open_channels_of_communication_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263448 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Open_channels_of_communication_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263448 320w" width="1960" height="1299" alt="Open channels of communication - Maintaining a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Open channels of communication - Maintaining a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-61_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-62_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Transparent communication is a hallmark of healthy company culture. Encourage teams to:</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-cbTzjv cdRhtw pf-64_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-65_ pf-text-1">Celebrate successes but also be open about failures. </li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-67_ pf-text-1">Hold regular feedback sessions, allowing employees at all levels to voice their opinions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-69_ pf-text-1">Foster a culture of constructive criticism, where employees can share feedback without fear. </li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-71_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-73_">Recognise and reward</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Recognise_and_reward_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263529" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Recognise_and_reward_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263529 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Recognise_and_reward_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263529 320w" width="1291" height="864" alt="Recognise and reward - Nurturing a positive company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Recognise and reward - Nurturing a positive company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-74_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-75_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Employees need to feel valued. Regular recognition and rewards motivate and help in retaining talent. This doesn’t always mean financial incentives; sometimes, a simple 'thank you' can go a long way.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-77_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-79_">Invest in employee growth</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Invest_in_employee_growth_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263618" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Invest_in_employee_growth_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263618 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Invest_in_employee_growth_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263618 320w" width="2400" height="1600" alt="Invest in employee growth - Building a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Invest in employee growth - Building a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-80_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-81_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Your employees are your biggest asset. Investing in their growth means:</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-cbTzjv cdRhtw pf-83_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-84_ pf-text-1">Regular training sessions to upskill. </li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-86_ pf-text-1">Opportunities for career advancement.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-88_ pf-text-1">Workshops on soft skills like communication, leadership, and conflict resolution. </li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-90_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-92_">Encourage work-life balance</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Encourage_work-life_balance_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263741" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Encourage_work-life_balance_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263741 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Encourage_work-life_balance_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263741 320w" width="2000" height="1500" alt="Encourage work-life balance - What is great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Encourage work-life balance - What is great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-93_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-94_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Burnout is real and can erode company culture quickly. Encourage employees to take breaks, use their vacation time, and disconnect after work hours. A happy, well-rested employee is more productive and contributes positively to the culture.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eGRUor ihBYJb pf-96_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iIUQWv fDZbFm pf-98_">Review and evolve</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Review_and_evolve_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263828" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Review_and_evolve_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692263828 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Review_and_evolve_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692263828 320w" width="2000" height="1500" alt="Review and evolve to acquire a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Review and evolve to acquire a great company culture - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-ilfuhL fjsXRa pf-99_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-100_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">A great company culture isn't static; it evolves. Regularly review your practices, seek feedback, and be willing to make necessary changes.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ctqQKy eJZCTA pf-102_ pf-heading-1-h3">Incorporating diversity and inclusion</h3><p class="sc-dFtzxp kO